LexVault Mesh
Distributed Legal Discovery & Evidence Intelligence Powered by QVAC
Tagline
Private Legal Intelligence Across Devices. No Cloud. No Data Leakage.
________________________________________
Executive Summary
LexVault Mesh is a fully local, multi-agent legal discovery and evidence intelligence platform that transforms large collections of legal documents, communications, and evidence into structured case knowledge without sending any data to the cloud.
Built using the QVAC SDK, LexVault Mesh distributes AI workloads across consumer devices through peer-to-peer delegation. A smartphone, laptop, and desktop collaborate as an intelligent investigation network capable of processing thousands of messages, contracts, emails, PDFs, and screenshots while preserving confidentiality.
The platform demonstrates how local-first AI can solve one of the most privacy-sensitive problems in the world: legal discovery and evidence analysis.
________________________________________
The Problem
Legal professionals, investigators, compliance teams, and businesses routinely work with:
•	WhatsApp exports
•	Emails
•	Contracts
•	Court filings
•	PDF evidence bundles
•	Screenshots
•	Financial records
Current AI-powered document analysis solutions require uploading highly sensitive information to centralized cloud providers.
This creates serious concerns:
•	Client confidentiality risks
•	Regulatory restrictions
•	Data residency issues
•	Vendor lock-in
•	High API costs
•	Exposure of privileged information
For many legal and investigative workflows, cloud AI is not an acceptable option.
________________________________________
The Solution
LexVault Mesh creates a distributed intelligence network that runs entirely on consumer hardware.
Instead of relying on cloud inference, specialized AI agents collaborate across devices using QVAC's local-first architecture.
Device Mesh
Mobile Device
•	Document capture
•	OCR preprocessing
•	Image analysis
•	Voice notes
Laptop
•	Embeddings generation
•	Vector indexing
•	RAG retrieval
•	Knowledge graph construction
Desktop / Workstation
•	Deep reasoning
•	Contradiction detection
•	Chronology generation
•	Legal brief synthesis
All communication occurs through QVAC-powered local and peer-to-peer infrastructure.
No evidence leaves the user's control.
________________________________________
Multi-Agent Architecture
Evidence Agent
Extracts entities, dates, people, organizations, locations, and events.
Timeline Agent
Builds chronological event sequences across thousands of documents.
Contradiction Agent
Identifies conflicting statements and inconsistencies.
Research Agent
Performs local RAG retrieval across case materials.
Briefing Agent
Generates investigation summaries and legal briefing documents.
Orchestration Agent
Coordinates workload distribution across available devices.
________________________________________
Example Workflow
A user uploads:
•	10,000 WhatsApp messages
•	200 PDFs
•	50 contracts
•	100 screenshots
LexVault Mesh automatically:
1.	Extracts and indexes evidence.
2.	Builds a searchable knowledge graph.
3.	Generates a case chronology.
4.	Identifies key actors and relationships.
5.	Detects contradictions and anomalies.
6.	Produces an investigation-ready briefing package.
All processing occurs locally.
